-- Lions Gate Estimates ‘Hunger Games’ Sales $155 Mln for 3 Days
-- B y   D a n   H a r t
-- 2012-03-25T14:35:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-25/lions-gate-estimates-hunger-games-sales-155-mln-for-3-days.html
Lions Gate Entertainment Corp. (LGF)  said
it estimated $155 million in gross receipts for “The Hunger
Games” for its opening weekend.  The film was expected to earn $125 million to $135 million
this weekend, analysts estimated.  Paul Dergarabedian , president
of Hollywood.com’s Box-Office division, yesterday said the film
may have a take of $140 million for Friday through Sunday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Dan Hart  at 
 dahart@bloomberg.net  